---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
const base = import.meta.env.BASE_URL.replace(/\/$/, '');
---

<Layout
  title="The Experiment"
  description="How the CAL DMRadio experiment works: toroidal LC resonator, SQUID amplifiers, and quantum-limited axion searches."
>

  <!-- Page header -->
  <section class="page-header">
    <div class="container">
      <span class="eyebrow">CAL DMRadio</span>
      <h1>The Experiment</h1>
      <p class="desc">
        A toroidal lumped-element resonator coupled to quantum-limited SQUID amplifiers,
        searching for the electromagnetic imprint of axion dark matter.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Overview -->
  <section class="section">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="two-col-60">
        <div>
          <span class="section-label">Overview</span>
          <h2 style="margin-bottom:1.25rem;">How DMRadio Works</h2>
          <p style="margin-bottom:1.25rem;">
            [Replace with 2&ndash;3 paragraphs from the DMRadio paper or proposal describing the
            operating principle. Key points to cover: axion-photon conversion in a static magnetic
            field, the pickup coil geometry, the signal chain, and why a toroidal design suppresses
            systematic backgrounds.]
          </p>
          <p style="margin-bottom:1.25rem;">
            [Second paragraph: describe the LC resonator, its resonant frequency, quality factor,
            and how tuning is achieved to scan across the target mass range.]
          </p>
          <p style="margin-bottom:1.25rem;">
            [Third paragraph: describe the SQUID-based amplifier chain, operating temperature
            (millikelvin), and how quantum-limited or sub-quantum-limited noise is achieved.]
          </p>
        </div>
        <div style="display:flex;flex-direction:column;gap:1rem;">
          <div class="diagram-placeholder">
            <p><strong>Detector schematic</strong></p>
            <p>Toroidal pickup coil + SQUID chain</p>
          </div>
          <div class="info-box">
            <h4 style="margin-bottom:0.5rem;">Key Parameters</h4>
            <table style="width:100%;border-collapse:collapse;font-size:0.875rem;">
              <tr><td style="padding:0.3rem 0;color:var(--gray-500);">Mass range</td><td style="color:var(--gray-900);font-weight:500;">[X &ndash; Y] &mu;eV</td></tr>
              <tr><td style="padding:0.3rem 0;color:var(--gray-500);">Frequency</td><td style="color:var(--gray-900);font-weight:500;">[X &ndash; Y] MHz</td></tr>
              <tr><td style="padding:0.3rem 0;color:var(--gray-500);">Temperature</td><td style="color:var(--gray-900);font-weight:500;">[X] mK</td></tr>
              <tr><td style="padding:0.3rem 0;color:var(--gray-500);">Magnetic field</td><td style="color:var(--gray-900);font-weight:500;">[X] T</td></tr>
              <tr><td style="padding:0.3rem 0;color:var(--gray-500);">Noise level</td><td style="color:var(--gray-900);font-weight:500;">Near SQL</td></tr>
            </table>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <hr class="divider">

  <!-- What it searches for -->
  <section class="section">
    <div class="container">
      <span class="section-label">Science Target</span>
      <h2 style="margin-bottom:1.25rem;">What We Search For</h2>
      <div class="two-col">
        <div>
          <h3 style="margin-bottom:0.75rem;">QCD Axions</h3>
          <p style="margin-bottom:1rem;">
            [Replace with description of the QCD axion as a dark matter candidate: the strong CP
            problem, Peccei-Quinn symmetry, and the predicted mass-coupling relationship along the
            DFSZ and KSVZ model lines.]
          </p>
          <p>
            DMRadio's target mass range of [X&ndash;Y] &mu;eV is motivated by [explain mass window
            motivation: cosmological production, misalignment mechanism, etc.].
          </p>
        </div>
        <div>
          <h3 style="margin-bottom:0.75rem;">Dark Photons & ALPs</h3>
          <p style="margin-bottom:1rem;">
            [Replace with description of axion-like particles (ALPs) and dark photons as additional
            search targets. Explain how DMRadio's sensitivity extends to these candidates and what
            parameter space it probes.]
          </p>
          <p>
            [Sensitivity projection: reference figure or table from the DMRadio sensitivity paper
            (arXiv:2104.09594).]
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <hr class="divider">

  <!-- Setup / hardware -->
  <section class="section">
    <div class="container">
      <span class="section-label">Hardware</span>
      <h2 style="margin-bottom:2.5rem;">Detector Setup</h2>
      <div class="grid-3">
        <div class="card">
          <h3 style="margin-bottom:0.75rem;color:var(--blue);">Toroidal Resonator</h3>
          <p style="font-size:0.9rem;">
            [Describe the toroidal pickup coil geometry, its advantages for suppressing spurious
            electromagnetic modes, the inductor-capacitor circuit, and the ferromagnetic or
            superconducting materials used.]
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="card">
          <h3 style="margin-bottom:0.75rem;color:var(--blue);">SQUID Amplifiers</h3>
          <p style="font-size:0.9rem;">
            [Describe the DC SQUID or rf-SQUID amplifier chain, how it couples to the resonator,
            the achieved noise temperature, and the role of quantum squeezing in reaching sub-SQL
            sensitivity.]
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="card">
          <h3 style="margin-bottom:0.75rem;color:var(--blue);">Cryogenic System</h3>
          <p style="font-size:0.9rem;">
            [Describe the dilution refrigerator, operating temperature, vibration isolation, and
            magnetic shielding. Reference the specific cryostat model and any custom hardware.]
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="card">
          <h3 style="margin-bottom:0.75rem;color:var(--blue);">Magnet</h3>
          <p style="font-size:0.9rem;">
            [Describe the superconducting magnet: field strength, bore size, orientation, and
            how it generates the static B-field required for axion-photon conversion.]
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="card">
          <h3 style="margin-bottom:0.75rem;color:var(--blue);">Data Acquisition</h3>
          <p style="font-size:0.9rem;">
            [Describe the DAQ chain: digitizers, sampling rate, data volume, the analysis
            pipeline, and the search algorithm used to look for the narrow axion signal
            above the noise floor.]
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="card">
          <h3 style="margin-bottom:0.75rem;color:var(--blue);">Analysis Pipeline</h3>
          <p style="font-size:0.9rem;">
            [Describe the offline analysis: power spectral density estimation, candidate
            identification, veto procedures, and the statistical framework for setting
            exclusion limits.]
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <hr class="divider">

  <!-- Challenges -->
  <section class="section">
    <div class="container">
      <span class="section-label">Engineering</span>
      <h2 style="margin-bottom:2rem;">Challenges &amp; Mitigations</h2>
      <div class="grid-2">
        <div class="info-box">
          <h4 style="margin-bottom:0.5rem;">Thermal Noise</h4>
          <p style="font-size:0.9rem;">
            [Describe how Johnson-Nyquist noise from resistive elements in the circuit is
            mitigated by operating at millikelvin temperatures and how residual noise is
            accounted for in the analysis.]
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="info-box">
          <h4 style="margin-bottom:0.5rem;">Vibrational Interference</h4>
          <p style="font-size:0.9rem;">
            [Describe mechanical vibration from the pulse tube cooler or cryostat, and the
            isolation strategies employed (springs, dampers, separate platforms).]
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="info-box">
          <h4 style="margin-bottom:0.5rem;">RF Interference</h4>
          <p style="font-size:0.9rem;">
            [Describe the electromagnetic shielding strategy, Faraday cage, filtering on
            cabling, and techniques for identifying and vetoing anthropogenic RFI in the data.]
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="info-box">
          <h4 style="margin-bottom:0.5rem;">Frequency Tuning</h4>
          <p style="font-size:0.9rem;">
            [Explain how the resonant frequency is tuned to scan across the target mass range,
            including variable capacitors, mechanical tuning, or other methods employed.]
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- CTA -->
  <section class="section-sm" style="background:var(--gray-50);border-top:1px solid var(--gray-200);">
    <div class="container" style="text-align:center;">
      <h3 style="margin-bottom:0.75rem;">Want to learn more?</h3>
      <p style="margin-bottom:1.5rem;max-width:500px;margin-left:auto;margin-right:auto;">
        Read our publications or reach out to join the collaboration.
      </p>
      <div style="display:flex;gap:1rem;justify-content:center;flex-wrap:wrap;">
        <a href={`${base}/publications/`} class="btn btn-primary">Publications</a>
        <a href={`${base}/opportunities/`} class="btn btn-secondary">Join Us</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

</Layout>
